    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I know the question is about getting the day of week as string (e.g. the short name), but for anybody who is looking for the numeric day of week (as I was), you can use the new \"u\" format string, supported since Java 7. For example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>new SimpleDateFormat(\"u\").format(new Date());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>returns today's day-of-week index, namely: 1 = Monday, 2 = Tuesday, ..., 7 = Sunday.</p>\n"
  } ],
